==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Crenel
<hw>Cre*nel"</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(kr?-n?l")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>crenel</ets>, F.
<ets>cr<?/neau</ets>, LL. <ets>crenellus</ets>, <ets>kernellus</ets>,
dim. (prob.) fr. L. <ets>crena</ets> notch. See <er>Crenny</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An embrasure or indentation in a battlement; a loophole
in a fortress; an indentation; a notch. See <er>Merlon</er>, and
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Battlement</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Crenature</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crenelled</ent>⟦br⟧
